Yesterday marked the closure of a very long chapter in my life. After 12 years on active duty and 3 years in the reserves, I am officially a civilian.

I would say the feeling is definitely bittersweet. Too many memories to list. Too many friendships to count. Too many feelings to express.

The one thing I do know though, is this chapter helped shape who I am today and prepared me to write the many more yet to come.

On to the next adventure! 🤙🏼

#militaryveteran #freedom #militarylife #wileyx #lifestories #rltw

I was just a young boy in school when this tragic event took place. I remember the day vividly, but didn’t comprehend the travesty the way my parents did.

As the years went by I grew to fully understand the depth of what happened and shaped a lot of the direction and choices I’ve made over the last two decades.

Earlier this year I had the honor to visit the memorial and pay my respects to the men and women who lost their lives due to this tragedy and to the men and women who sacrificed their lives trying to save them.

My children were not around when this took place, but I continue to educate them and enlighten them on the events of September 11th and the impact it had and continues to have on our nation. This way we will never forget.

#September11 #911memorial #NeverForget
